:End Note

Note:
This file handles syntax highlighting and IDE syntax integration.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process syntax highlighting and IDE syntax integration
- Handle syntax tokenization and syntax color management
- Manage syntax themes and syntax formatting
- Process syntax communication and syntax protocol implementation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Syntax highlighting enables IDE syntax integration and syntax support
- Proper syntax highlighting ensures correct syntax color display
- Syntax highlighting support enables Runa compilation for IDE-integrated syntax handling

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Semantic token generation from Runa source code
- LSP semantic token encoding (delta-encoded line/column/length)
- Token type classification for Runa language elements
- Token type legend for client registration
- Full document tokenization for syntax highlighting

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa for owned-heap allocate/deallocate and raw memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for token list management
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as MemoryLayout
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Semantic Token Data Structures
Note: ============================================================================

Note: SemanticToken structure (40 bytes total, 5 fields x 8 bytes each)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  line (8 bytes) - Zero-based absolute line number
Note:   offset 8:  col (8 bytes) - Zero-based absolute column number
Note:   offset 16: length (8 bytes) - Length of the token in characters
Note:   offset 24: token_type (8 bytes) - Token type constant (TOKEN_KEYWORD, etc.)
Note:   offset 32: modifiers (8 bytes) - Bitmask of token modifiers

Type called "SemanticToken":
    line as Integer
    col as Integer
    length as Integer
    token_type as Integer
    modifiers as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Type Constants (must match the legend sent during initialization)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant TOKEN_KEYWORD as Integer is 0
Constant TOKEN_TYPE_NAME as Integer is 1
Constant TOKEN_FUNCTION as Integer is 2
Constant TOKEN_VARIABLE as Integer is 3
Constant TOKEN_STRING as Integer is 4
Constant TOKEN_NUMBER as Integer is 5
Constant TOKEN_COMMENT as Integer is 6
Constant TOKEN_ANNOTATION as Integer is 7
Constant TOKEN_OPERATOR as Integer is 8

Note: Token modifier bitmask constants
Constant MODIFIER_NONE as Integer is 0
Constant MODIFIER_DECLARATION as Integer is 1
Constant MODIFIER_DEFINITION as Integer is 2
Constant MODIFIER_READONLY as Integer is 4
Constant MODIFIER_STATIC as Integer is 8
Constant MODIFIER_DEPRECATED as Integer is 16

Note: Total number of token types in the legend
Constant TOKEN_TYPE_COUNT as Integer is 9

Note: Maximum semantic tokens per document
Constant MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS as Integer is 65536

Note: Return codes
Constant HIGHLIGHT_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant HIGHLIGHT_FAILED as Integer is -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Core Tokenization
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "tokenize_for_highlighting" takes document_text as Integer, doc_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Tokenize a Runa document for semantic highlighting
    Note: Scans the document character by character and classifies each token
    Note: into one of the semantic token types (keyword, string, comment, etc.)
    
    Note: Classification rules:
    Note: - "Note:" through end of line -> TOKEN_COMMENT
    Note: - Quoted strings ("...") -> TOKEN_STRING
    Note: - Digit sequences -> TOKEN_NUMBER
    Note: - "@" followed by identifier -> TOKEN_ANNOTATION
    Note: - Runa keywords (Let, Set, If, etc.) -> TOKEN_KEYWORD
    Note: - Identifiers after "Process called" -> TOKEN_FUNCTION
    Note: - Identifiers after "Type called" -> TOKEN_TYPE_NAME
    Note: - Identifiers after operators/keywords -> TOKEN_VARIABLE
    Note: - Operators (+, -, *, /, etc.) -> TOKEN_OPERATOR
    
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   document_text - Pointer to full document text
    Note:   doc_len - Length of document text
    
    Note: Returns pointer to result array (data_ptr, count, capacity) of SemanticToken pointers
    Note: Returns 0 on failure

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result structure
    Let result be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let tokens_array be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS multiplied by 8
    If tokens_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with result
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 0, tokens_array
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 8, 0
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 16, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS

    Let pos be 0
    Let current_line be 0
    Let current_col be 0
    Let token_count be 0

    While pos is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos

        Note: Track newlines
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
            Set current_col to 0
            Set pos to pos plus 1

        Note: Skip whitespace (but track column)
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 32:
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 9:
            Set current_col to current_col plus 4
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 13:
            Set pos to pos plus 1

        Note: String literals
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 34:
            Let str_start_col be current_col
            Let str_start be pos
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            Note: Scan to closing quote
            Let in_escape be 0
            While pos is less than doc_len:
                Let sc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                If in_escape is equal to 1:
                    Set in_escape to 0
                Otherwise If sc is equal to 92:
                    Set in_escape to 1
                Otherwise If sc is equal to 34:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                    Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                Otherwise If sc is equal to 10:
                    Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                End If
                If pos is less than doc_len:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                End If
            End While
            If pos is greater than doc_len:
                Set pos to pos minus doc_len
            End If

            Let str_len be pos minus str_start
            If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                Let token be proc create_semantic_token with current_line, str_start_col, str_len, TOKEN_STRING, MODIFIER_NONE
                If token is not equal to 0:
                    Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                    Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

        Note: Comments (starts with "Note:")
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 78:
            Note: Check for "Note:" (N=78, o=111, t=116, e=101, :=58)
            If pos plus 4 is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos plus 1
                Let c2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos plus 2
                Let c3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos plus 3
                Let c4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos plus 4
                If c1 is equal to 111:
                    If c2 is equal to 116:
                        If c3 is equal to 101:
                            If c4 is equal to 58:
                                Note: Found "Note:" - scan to end of line (single-line comment token)
                                Let comment_start_col be current_col
                                Let comment_start be pos
                                While pos is less than doc_len:
                                    Let cc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                                    If cc is equal to 10:
                                        Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                                        Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                                    End If
                                End While
                                If pos is greater than doc_len:
                                    Set pos to pos minus doc_len
                                End If

                                Let comment_len be pos minus comment_start
                                If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                                    Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, comment_start_col, comment_len, TOKEN_COMMENT, MODIFIER_NONE
                                    If token is not equal to 0:
                                        Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                                        Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If

                                Note: Check whether this "Note:" is the OPENER of a block-form note.
                                Note: Block opener: the only non-whitespace content on the line is "Note:" itself.
                                Note: The 5 chars of "Note:" occupy [comment_start, comment_start + 5).
                                Note: Everything between (comment_start + 5) and pos must be whitespace.
                                Let note_body_start be comment_start plus 5
                                Let note_body_ws_only be proc range_is_ws_only with document_text, note_body_start, pos
                                If note_body_ws_only is equal to 1:
                                    Note: This is a block-form opener. Consume newline, then scan lines as
                                    Note: TOKEN_COMMENT until we consume a line whose trimmed content is ":End Note".
                                    If pos is less than doc_len:
                                        Let nl_check be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                                        If nl_check is equal to 10:
                                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                                            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
                                            Set current_col to 0
                                        End If
                                    End If

                                    Let note_block_done be 0
                                    While note_block_done is equal to 0:
                                        If pos is greater than doc_len minus 1:
                                            Set note_block_done to 1
                                        End If
                                        If note_block_done is equal to 0:
                                            Let line_start be pos
                                            Let line_start_col be current_col
                                            Note: Scan to end of line
                                            While pos is less than doc_len:
                                                Let lcc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                                                If lcc is equal to 10:
                                                    Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                                                    Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                                                End If
                                            End While
                                            Let line_had_newline be 0
                                            If pos is greater than doc_len:
                                                Set pos to pos minus doc_len
                                                Set line_had_newline to 1
                                            End If

                                            Let line_text_len be pos minus line_start
                                            If line_text_len is greater than 0:
                                                If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                                                    Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, line_start_col, line_text_len, TOKEN_COMMENT, MODIFIER_NONE
                                                    If token is not equal to 0:
                                                        Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                                                        Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                                                    End If
                                                End If
                                            End If

                                            Note: Check if this line trimmed equals ":End Note" (case-insensitive on letters).
                                            Let is_end_marker be proc line_matches_end_note with document_text, line_start, pos
                                            If is_end_marker is equal to 1:
                                                Set note_block_done to 1
                                            End If

                                            Note: Consume trailing newline (if any) and advance line/col.
                                            If line_had_newline is equal to 1:
                                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                                                Set current_line to current_line plus 1
                                                Set current_col to 0
                                            Otherwise:
                                                Set note_block_done to 1
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End While
                                End If
                            Otherwise:
                                Note: Not "Note:" - treat as identifier
                                Let ident_result be proc tokenize_identifier with document_text, doc_len, pos, current_line, current_col, tokens_array, token_count, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
                                Let new_pos be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 0
                                Let new_col be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 8
                                Let new_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 16
                                Set pos to new_pos
                                Set current_col to new_col
                                Set token_count to new_count
                                Let dummy_free_ir be proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with ident_result
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Set ident_result to proc tokenize_identifier with document_text, doc_len, pos, current_line, current_col, tokens_array, token_count, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
                            Set new_pos to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 0
                            Set new_col to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 8
                            Set new_count to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 16
                            Set pos to new_pos
                            Set current_col to new_col
                            Set token_count to new_count
                            Set dummy_free_ir to proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with ident_result
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        Set ident_result to proc tokenize_identifier with document_text, doc_len, pos, current_line, current_col, tokens_array, token_count, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
                        Set new_pos to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 0
                        Set new_col to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 8
                        Set new_count to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 16
                        Set pos to new_pos
                        Set current_col to new_col
                        Set token_count to new_count
                        Set dummy_free_ir to proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with ident_result
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            End If

        Note: Annotations (@)
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 64:
            Let ann_start_col be current_col
            Let ann_start be pos
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            Let ann_name_start be pos
            Note: Scan the annotation name (alphanumeric + underscore)
            While pos is less than doc_len:
                Let ac be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                Let is_ann_char be proc is_ident_char with ac
                If is_ann_char is equal to 0:
                    Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                Otherwise:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                End If
            End While
            If pos is greater than doc_len:
                Set pos to pos minus doc_len
            End If

            Let ann_name_len be pos minus ann_name_start
            Let ann_handled be 0

            Note: Check whether this is a recognized annotation followed by ':' (inline or block form).
            Let recognized be 0
            If ann_name_len is greater than 0:
                Set recognized to proc is_recognized_annotation_name with document_text, ann_name_start, ann_name_len
            End If
            If recognized is equal to 1:
                If pos is less than doc_len:
                    Let after_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                    If after_name is equal to 58:
                        Note: Found "@Name:" - consume ':' and decide inline vs block.
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                        Set current_col to current_col plus 1

                        Note: Scan to end of line, tracking where ':' ended for ws-only check.
                        Let after_colon_pos be pos
                        While pos is less than doc_len:
                            Let acc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                            If acc is equal to 10:
                                Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                            Otherwise:
                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                                Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                            End If
                        End While
                        Let ann_line_had_newline be 0
                        If pos is greater than doc_len:
                            Set pos to pos minus doc_len
                            Set ann_line_had_newline to 1
                        End If

                        Note: Emit ONE TOKEN_ANNOTATION for the entire opener/inline line from '@' to newline.
                        Let opener_len be pos minus ann_start
                        If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                            Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, ann_start_col, opener_len, TOKEN_ANNOTATION, MODIFIER_NONE
                            If token is not equal to 0:
                                Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                                Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        Note: Block opener if everything between after_colon_pos and pos is whitespace.
                        Let body_ws_only be proc range_is_ws_only with document_text, after_colon_pos, pos
                        If body_ws_only is equal to 1:
                            Note: Consume newline at end of opener.
                            If ann_line_had_newline is equal to 1:
                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                                Set current_line to current_line plus 1
                                Set current_col to 0
                            End If

                            Note: Scan subsequent lines as TOKEN_ANNOTATION until "@End <Name>" line consumed.
                            Let ann_block_done be 0
                            While ann_block_done is equal to 0:
                                If pos is greater than doc_len minus 1:
                                    Set ann_block_done to 1
                                End If
                                If ann_block_done is equal to 0:
                                    Let aline_start be pos
                                    Let aline_start_col be current_col
                                    While pos is less than doc_len:
                                        Let alcc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                                        If alcc is equal to 10:
                                            Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                                        Otherwise:
                                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                                            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                                        End If
                                    End While
                                    Let aline_had_newline be 0
                                    If pos is greater than doc_len:
                                        Set pos to pos minus doc_len
                                        Set aline_had_newline to 1
                                    End If

                                    Let aline_text_len be pos minus aline_start
                                    If aline_text_len is greater than 0:
                                        If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                                            Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, aline_start_col, aline_text_len, TOKEN_ANNOTATION, MODIFIER_NONE
                                            If token is not equal to 0:
                                                Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                                                Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If

                                    Note: Check if line trimmed equals "@End <Name>" (case-insensitive on letters).
                                    Let is_end_ann be proc line_matches_end_annotation with document_text, aline_start, pos, ann_name_start, ann_name_len
                                    If is_end_ann is equal to 1:
                                        Set ann_block_done to 1
                                    End If

                                    If aline_had_newline is equal to 1:
                                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                                        Set current_line to current_line plus 1
                                        Set current_col to 0
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Set ann_block_done to 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End While
                        End If
                        Set ann_handled to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            If ann_handled is equal to 0:
                Note: Fallback: emit a token covering just '@' + name (original behavior).
                Let ann_len be pos minus ann_start
                If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                    Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, ann_start_col, ann_len, TOKEN_ANNOTATION, MODIFIER_NONE
                    If token is not equal to 0:
                        Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                        Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If

        Note: Numbers
        Otherwise If ch is greater than 47:
            If ch is less than 58:
                Let num_start_col be current_col
                Let num_start be pos
                While pos is less than doc_len:
                    Let nc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, pos
                    Note: Digits and decimal point
                    Let is_digit be 0
                    If nc is greater than 47:
                        If nc is less than 58:
                            Set is_digit to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    If nc is equal to 46:
                        Set is_digit to 1
                    End If
                    If is_digit is equal to 0:
                        Set pos to pos plus doc_len
                    Otherwise:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                        Set current_col to current_col plus 1
                    End If
                End While
                If pos is greater than doc_len:
                    Set pos to pos minus doc_len
                End If

                Let num_len be pos minus num_start
                If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                    Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, num_start_col, num_len, TOKEN_NUMBER, MODIFIER_NONE
                    If token is not equal to 0:
                        Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                        Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Note: Regular identifier or keyword
                Set ident_result to proc tokenize_identifier with document_text, doc_len, pos, current_line, current_col, tokens_array, token_count, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
                Set new_pos to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 0
                Set new_col to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 8
                Set new_count to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 16
                Set pos to new_pos
                Set current_col to new_col
                Set token_count to new_count
                Set dummy_free_ir to proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with ident_result
            End If

        Note: Operators
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 43:
            Note: Plus
            If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, current_col, 1, TOKEN_OPERATOR, MODIFIER_NONE
                If token is not equal to 0:
                    Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                    Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 45:
            Note: Minus
            If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, current_col, 1, TOKEN_OPERATOR, MODIFIER_NONE
                If token is not equal to 0:
                    Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                    Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 42:
            Note: Asterisk
            If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, current_col, 1, TOKEN_OPERATOR, MODIFIER_NONE
                If token is not equal to 0:
                    Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                    Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 47:
            Note: Slash
            If token_count is less than MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS:
                Set token to proc create_semantic_token with current_line, current_col, 1, TOKEN_OPERATOR, MODIFIER_NONE
                If token is not equal to 0:
                    Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, token_count multiplied by 8, token
                    Set token_count to token_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set current_col to current_col plus 1

        Note: Identifiers and keywords (starts with letter or underscore)
        Otherwise:
            Let is_alpha be proc is_ident_char with ch
            If is_alpha is equal to 1:
                Set ident_result to proc tokenize_identifier with document_text, doc_len, pos, current_line, current_col, tokens_array, token_count, MAX_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
                Set new_pos to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 0
                Set new_col to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 8
                Set new_count to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with ident_result, 16
                Set pos to new_pos
                Set current_col to new_col
                Set token_count to new_count
                Set dummy_free_ir to proc deallocate from MemoryLayout with ident_result
            Otherwise:
                Note: Unknown character - skip it
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Let dummy_final_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 8, token_count
    Return result
End Process

Process called "encode_semantic_tokens" takes tokens_result as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Encode semantic tokens into the LSP delta-encoded format
    Note: LSP requires tokens as a flat array of 5-tuples:
    Note: [deltaLine, deltaStartChar, length, tokenType, tokenModifiers]
    Note: Each token's line and column are relative to the previous token
    
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   tokens_result - Pointer to result array from tokenize_for_highlighting
    
    Note: Returns pointer to flat integer array of encoded tokens
    Note: The first 8 bytes contain the total count of integers (count * 5)
    Note: Returns 0 on failure

    If tokens_result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let tokens_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_result, 0
    Let token_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_result, 8

    If token_count is equal to 0:
        Note: Return empty array
        Let empty be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
        If empty is not equal to 0:
            Let dummy_zero be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with empty, 0, 0
        End If
        Return empty
    End If

    Note: Allocate output: 8 bytes for count + 5 integers per token (each 8 bytes)
    Let output_size be 8 plus token_count multiplied by 5 multiplied by 8
    Let output be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with output_size
    If output is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Write total integer count
    Let total_ints be token_count multiplied by 5
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, 0, total_ints

    Note: Encode each token as delta values
    Let prev_line be 0
    Let prev_col be 0
    Let out_offset be 8

    Let ti be 0
    While ti is less than token_count:
        Let token_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_data, ti multiplied by 8
        If token_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let tok_line be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with token_ptr, 0
            Let tok_col be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with token_ptr, 8
            Let tok_len be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with token_ptr, 16
            Let tok_type be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with token_ptr, 24
            Let tok_mods be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with token_ptr, 32

            Note: Calculate deltas
            Let delta_line be tok_line minus prev_line
            Let delta_col be tok_col
            If delta_line is equal to 0:
                Set delta_col to tok_col minus prev_col
            End If

            Note: Write the 5-tuple
            Let dummy_dl be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, out_offset, delta_line
            Set out_offset to out_offset plus 8
            Let dummy_dc be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, out_offset, delta_col
            Set out_offset to out_offset plus 8
            Let dummy_tl be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, out_offset, tok_len
            Set out_offset to out_offset plus 8
            Let dummy_tt be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, out_offset, tok_type
            Set out_offset to out_offset plus 8
            Let dummy_tm be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with output, out_offset, tok_mods
            Set out_offset to out_offset plus 8

            Note: Update previous position
            Set prev_line to tok_line
            Set prev_col to tok_col
        End If
        Set ti to ti plus 1
    End While

    Return output
End Process

Process called "get_token_type_legend" returns Integer:
    Note: Return the semantic token type legend for LSP registration
    Note: The legend maps token type indices to their string names
    Note: This must match the TOKEN_* constants defined above
    
    Note: Legend order (matching constant values):
    Note:   0: "keyword"
    Note:   1: "type"
    Note:   2: "function"
    Note:   3: "variable"
    Note:   4: "string"
    Note:   5: "number"
    Note:   6: "comment"
    Note:   7: "decorator" (annotation)
    Note:   8: "operator"
    
    Note: Returns pointer to array of string pointers (9 entries)
    Note: Returns 0 on allocation failure

    Let legend be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with TOKEN_TYPE_COUNT multiplied by 8
    If legend is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create each legend entry string
    Note: "keyword" k=107 e=101 y=121 w=119 o=111 r=114 d=100
    Let kw_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
    If kw_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_k be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 0, 107
        Let dummy_e be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 1, 101
        Let dummy_y be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 2, 121
        Let dummy_w be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 3, 119
        Let dummy_o be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 4, 111
        Let dummy_r be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 5, 114
        Let dummy_d be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 6, 100
        Let dummy_t be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with kw_str, 7, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l0 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 0, kw_str

    Note: "type" t=116 y=121 p=112 e=101
    Let type_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
    If type_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_t1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with type_str, 0, 116
        Let dummy_y1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with type_str, 1, 121
        Let dummy_p1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with type_str, 2, 112
        Let dummy_e1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with type_str, 3, 101
        Let dummy_term1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with type_str, 4, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 8, type_str

    Note: "function" f=102 u=117 n=110 c=99 t=116 i=105 o=111 n=110
    Let func_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 12
    If func_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_f1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 0, 102
        Let dummy_u1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 1, 117
        Let dummy_n1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 2, 110
        Let dummy_c1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 3, 99
        Let dummy_t2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 4, 116
        Let dummy_i1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 5, 105
        Let dummy_o1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 6, 111
        Let dummy_n2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 7, 110
        Let dummy_term2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with func_str, 8, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 16, func_str

    Note: "variable" v=118 a=97 r=114 i=105 a=97 b=98 l=108 e=101
    Let var_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 12
    If var_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_v1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 0, 118
        Let dummy_a1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 1, 97
        Let dummy_r1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 2, 114
        Let dummy_i2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 3, 105
        Let dummy_a2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 4, 97
        Let dummy_b1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 5, 98
        Set dummy_l1 to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 6, 108
        Let dummy_e2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 7, 101
        Let dummy_term3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with var_str, 8, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 24, var_str

    Note: "string" s=115 t=116 r=114 i=105 n=110 g=103
    Let str_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
    If str_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_s1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 0, 115
        Let dummy_t3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 1, 116
        Let dummy_r2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 2, 114
        Let dummy_i3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 3, 105
        Let dummy_n3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 4, 110
        Let dummy_g1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 5, 103
        Let dummy_term4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with str_str, 6, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 32, str_str

    Note: "number" n=110 u=117 m=109 b=98 e=101 r=114
    Let num_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
    If num_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_n4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 0, 110
        Let dummy_u2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 1, 117
        Let dummy_m1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 2, 109
        Let dummy_b2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 3, 98
        Let dummy_e3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 4, 101
        Let dummy_r3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 5, 114
        Let dummy_term5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with num_str, 6, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 40, num_str

    Note: "comment" c=99 o=111 m=109 m=109 e=101 n=110 t=116
    Let comment_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 8
    If comment_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_c2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 0, 99
        Let dummy_o2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 1, 111
        Let dummy_m2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 2, 109
        Let dummy_m3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 3, 109
        Let dummy_e4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 4, 101
        Let dummy_n5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 5, 110
        Let dummy_t4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 6, 116
        Let dummy_term6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with comment_str, 7, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 48, comment_str

    Note: "decorator" (for annotations) d=100 e=101 c=99 o=111 r=114 a=97 t=116 o=111 r=114
    Let deco_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 12
    If deco_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_d2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 0, 100
        Let dummy_e5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 1, 101
        Let dummy_c3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 2, 99
        Let dummy_o3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 3, 111
        Let dummy_r4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 4, 114
        Let dummy_a3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 5, 97
        Let dummy_t5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 6, 116
        Let dummy_o4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 7, 111
        Let dummy_r5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 8, 114
        Let dummy_term7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with deco_str, 9, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 56, deco_str

    Note: "operator" o=111 p=112 e=101 r=114 a=97 t=116 o=111 r=114
    Let op_str be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 12
    If op_str is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_o5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 0, 111
        Let dummy_p2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 1, 112
        Let dummy_e6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 2, 101
        Let dummy_r6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 3, 114
        Let dummy_a4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 4, 97
        Let dummy_t6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 5, 116
        Let dummy_o6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 6, 111
        Let dummy_r7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 7, 114
        Let dummy_term8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with op_str, 8, 0
    End If
    Let dummy_l8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with legend, 64, op_str

    Return legend
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Processes
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_semantic_token" takes line as Integer, col as Integer, length as Integer, token_type as Integer, modifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a SemanticToken structure (40 bytes)

    Let token be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 40
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_line be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with token, 0, line
    Let dummy_col be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with token, 8, col
    Let dummy_len be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with token, 16, length
    Let dummy_type be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with token, 24, token_type
    Let dummy_mods be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with token, 32, modifiers

    Return token
End Process

Process called "is_ident_char" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if character is valid in an identifier
    If ch is greater than 96:
        If ch is less than 123:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than 64:
        If ch is less than 91:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than 47:
        If ch is less than 58:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is equal to 95:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "is_keyword" takes word_start as Integer, word_len as Integer, document_text as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if the word at the given position is a Runa keyword
    Note: Returns 1 if keyword, 0 if not
    Note: Checks against known Runa keywords by first character and length

    If word_len is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If
    If word_len is greater than 10:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, word_start

    Note: Check common keywords
    Note: "Let" (L=76, 3 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 76:
        If word_len is equal to 3:
            Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, word_start plus 1
            If c1 is equal to 101:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Set" (S=83, 3 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 83:
        If word_len is equal to 3:
            Set c1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, word_start plus 1
            If c1 is equal to 101:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "If" (I=73, 2 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 73:
        If word_len is equal to 2:
            Set c1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, word_start plus 1
            If c1 is equal to 102:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Note: "Import" (6 chars)
        If word_len is equal to 6:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "End" (E=69, 3 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 69:
        If word_len is equal to 3:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Otherwise" (O=79, 9 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 79:
        If word_len is equal to 9:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "While" (W=87, 5 chars), "When" (4 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 87:
        If word_len is equal to 5:
            Return 1
        End If
        If word_len is equal to 4:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "For" (F=70, 3 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 70:
        If word_len is equal to 3:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Return" (R=82, 6 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 82:
        If word_len is equal to 6:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Process" (P=80, 7 chars), "Private" (7 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 80:
        If word_len is equal to 7:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Type" (T=84, 4 chars), "Try" (3 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 84:
        If word_len is equal to 4:
            Return 1
        End If
        If word_len is equal to 3:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Constant" (C=67, 8 chars), "Catch" (5 chars), "Continue" (8 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 67:
        If word_len is equal to 8:
            Return 1
        End If
        If word_len is equal to 5:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Match" (M=77, 5 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 77:
        If word_len is equal to 5:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: "Break" (B=66, 5 chars)
    If first_ch is equal to 66:
        If word_len is equal to 5:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "tokenize_identifier" takes document_text as Integer, doc_len as Integer, pos as Integer, current_line as Integer, current_col as Integer, tokens_array as Integer, token_count as Integer, max_tokens as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Tokenize an identifier or keyword starting at pos
    Note: Returns a 24-byte result struct: [new_pos, new_col, new_token_count]

    Let result be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Note: Skip the character on failure
        Let fallback be proc allocate from MemoryLayout with 24
        If fallback is not equal to 0:
            Let dummy_p be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with fallback, 0, pos plus 1
            Let dummy_c be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with fallback, 8, current_col plus 1
            Let dummy_tc be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with fallback, 16, token_count
        End If
        Return fallback
    End If

    Let ident_start be pos
    Let ident_start_col be current_col
    Let scan_pos be pos

    Note: Scan the full identifier
    While scan_pos is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan_pos
        Let is_id be proc is_ident_char with ch
        If is_id is equal to 0:
            Set scan_pos to scan_pos plus doc_len
        Otherwise:
            Set scan_pos to scan_pos plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If scan_pos is greater than doc_len:
        Set scan_pos to scan_pos minus doc_len
    End If

    Let ident_len be scan_pos minus ident_start
    Let new_col be current_col plus ident_len

    Note: Classify the token
    Let tok_type be TOKEN_VARIABLE
    Let is_kw be proc is_keyword with ident_start, ident_len, document_text
    If is_kw is equal to 1:
        Set tok_type to TOKEN_KEYWORD
    End If

    Note: Create and store the token
    Let new_token_count be token_count
    If new_token_count is less than max_tokens:
        Let token be proc create_semantic_token with current_line, ident_start_col, ident_len, tok_type, MODIFIER_NONE
        If token is not equal to 0:
            Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with tokens_array, new_token_count multiplied by 8, token
            Set new_token_count to new_token_count plus 1
        End If
    End If

    Let dummy_pos be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 0, scan_pos
    Let dummy_col be proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 8, new_col
    Set dummy_tc to proc memory_set_integer from MemoryLayout with result, 16, new_token_count

    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Block-Form Comment and Annotation Helpers
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "is_ws_byte" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns 1 if ch is a horizontal-whitespace byte (space, tab, carriage return).
    Newlines are intentionally NOT whitespace here: callers use newline as a line
    terminator and need to detect it separately.

    Implementation: Compares against ASCII 32 (space), 9 (tab), and 13 (CR).
    :End Note

    If ch is equal to 32:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 9:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 13:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "range_is_ws_only" takes document_text as Integer, range_start as Integer, range_end as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Tests whether every byte in the half-open range starting at range_start and ending
    at range_end is horizontal whitespace.
    Used by the block-form openers (the bare Note opener and the bare annotation opener)
    to decide whether the tokenized line was an opener or single-line content.

    Implementation: Empty range returns 1 (vacuously whitespace-only). Iterates byte by
    byte; bails to 0 on the first non-whitespace byte. Reuses is_ws_byte.
    :End Note

    If range_end is less than range_start plus 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let scan be range_start
    Let result be 1
    While scan is less than range_end:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
        Let ws be proc is_ws_byte with ch
        If ws is equal to 0:
            Set result to 0
            Set scan to range_end
        Otherwise:
            Set scan to scan plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Return result
End Process

Process called "lc_byte" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns the lowercase variant of ch if ch is an ASCII uppercase letter, otherwise
    returns ch unchanged. Used by case-insensitive literal comparison for end markers
    such as the closer of a Note block or the closer of an annotation block.

    Implementation: ASCII uppercase letters occupy decimal codes 65 through 90 inclusive.
    Adding 32 converts to lowercase, which occupies decimal codes 97 through 122.
    :End Note

    If ch is greater than 64:
        If ch is less than 91:
            Return ch plus 32
        End If
    End If
    Return ch
End Process

Process called "skip_leading_ws" takes document_text as Integer, range_start as Integer, range_end as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns the smallest offset at or above range_start, below range_end, whose byte is
    not horizontal whitespace. If the range is entirely whitespace, or empty, returns
    range_end. Used by line_matches_end_note and line_matches_end_annotation to find
    the first non-whitespace character on a candidate end-marker line.

    Implementation: Loops from range_start. Bails out of the loop by jumping the cursor
    past range_end when a non-whitespace byte is found, then restores the cursor to that
    byte index after the loop completes. This mirrors the break idiom used elsewhere in
    this file.
    :End Note

    Let cursor be range_start
    While cursor is less than range_end:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, cursor
        Let ws be proc is_ws_byte with ch
        If ws is equal to 1:
            Set cursor to cursor plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set cursor to range_end plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If cursor is greater than range_end:
        Set cursor to cursor minus range_end minus 1
        Set cursor to cursor plus range_end
    End If
    Return cursor
End Process

Process called "line_matches_end_note" takes document_text as Integer, line_start as Integer, line_end as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns 1 if and only if the byte range from line_start up to but not including
    line_end is exactly the closer colon End Note surrounded by horizontal whitespace.
    The match on the letters of End and Note is case-insensitive; the colon and the
    separating space are required literally.

    Implementation steps:
    Step 1. Skip leading whitespace to find the first non-whitespace byte.
    Step 2. Require a colon byte at that position.
    Step 3. Require case-insensitive E, n, d for the word End.
    Step 4. Require a single space byte.
    Step 5. Require case-insensitive N, o, t, e for the word Note.
    Step 6. Require all remaining bytes up to line_end to be horizontal whitespace.
    :End Note

    Let scan be proc skip_leading_ws with document_text, line_start, line_end

    Note: Need at least 9 bytes for ":End Note".
    If scan plus 9 is greater than line_end plus 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scan plus 8 is greater than line_end:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b0 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    If b0 is equal to 58:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb1 be proc lc_byte with b1
    If lb1 is equal to 101:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb2 be proc lc_byte with b2
    If lb2 is equal to 110:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb3 be proc lc_byte with b3
    If lb3 is equal to 100:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    If b4 is equal to 32:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b5 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb5 be proc lc_byte with b5
    If lb5 is equal to 110:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b6 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb6 be proc lc_byte with b6
    If lb6 is equal to 111:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b7 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb7 be proc lc_byte with b7
    If lb7 is equal to 116:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b8 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb8 be proc lc_byte with b8
    If lb8 is equal to 101:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Remainder of line must be whitespace only.
    Let tail_ws be proc range_is_ws_only with document_text, scan, line_end
    Return tail_ws
End Process

Process called "match_name_ci" takes document_text as Integer, doc_start as Integer, name_chars as Integer, name_start as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Case-insensitively compares the byte sequence at doc_start through doc_start plus
    name_len against the byte sequence at name_start through name_start plus name_len.
    Both buffers are within the same document_text pointer.
    Returns 1 on full match, 0 otherwise.

    Implementation: Iterates name_len bytes, lowercasing each pair via lc_byte before
    equality compare. The name_chars parameter is unused but kept for signature symmetry
    with future literal forms; current callers pass zero.
    :End Note

    Let i be 0
    Let result be 1
    While i is less than name_len:
        Let a be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, doc_start plus i
        Let b be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, name_start plus i
        Let la be proc lc_byte with a
        Let lb be proc lc_byte with b
        If la is equal to lb:
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set result to 0
            Set i to name_len
        End If
    End While
    Return result
End Process

Process called "line_matches_end_annotation" takes document_text as Integer, line_start as Integer, line_end as Integer, name_start as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns 1 if and only if the byte range from line_start up to but not including
    line_end is exactly the closer at-sign End space Name. Name must match the original
    opener s name case-insensitively. The line must be surrounded only by horizontal
    whitespace. Used to terminate annotation-block scanning.

    Implementation steps:
    Step 1. Skip leading whitespace.
    Step 2. Require the at-sign byte at the first non-whitespace position.
    Step 3. Require case-insensitive E, n, d for End.
    Step 4. Require a single space byte.
    Step 5. Require the next name_len bytes to match the opener s name case-insensitively.
    Step 6. Require all remaining bytes up to line_end to be horizontal whitespace.
    :End Note

    Let scan be proc skip_leading_ws with document_text, line_start, line_end

    Note: Need at least 5 + name_len bytes for "@End " + Name.
    Let needed be 5 plus name_len
    If scan plus needed is greater than line_end plus 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scan plus needed minus 1 is greater than line_end minus 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b0 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    If b0 is equal to 64:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb1 be proc lc_byte with b1
    If lb1 is equal to 101:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb2 be proc lc_byte with b2
    If lb2 is equal to 110:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    Let lb3 be proc lc_byte with b3
    If lb3 is equal to 100:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let b4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, scan
    If b4 is equal to 32:
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compare the trailing name bytes case-insensitively against the opener's name.
    Let name_matches be proc match_name_ci with document_text, scan, 0, name_start, name_len
    If name_matches is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set scan to scan plus name_len

    Note: Remainder of line must be whitespace only.
    Let tail_ws be proc range_is_ws_only with document_text, scan, line_end
    Return tail_ws
End Process

Process called "match_literal_ci_letters" takes document_text as Integer, doc_start as Integer, doc_len_limit as Integer, lit0 as Integer, lit1 as Integer, lit2 as Integer, lit3 as Integer, lit4 as Integer, lit5 as Integer, lit6 as Integer, lit7 as Integer, lit_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Case-insensitively compares lit_len bytes of document_text starting at doc_start
    against a literal letter sequence supplied as up to eight individual lowercase ASCII
    codes. Trailing slots beyond lit_len are ignored. This pattern avoids allocating
    literal-string buffers for short annotation names. For names longer than eight letters
    callers should use match_literal_ci_long, which reads the literal from a buffer.

    Implementation: Iterates lit_len positions comparing the lowercased document byte to
    the corresponding literal slot via lc_byte. doc_len_limit guards against
    out-of-bounds reads.
    :End Note

    If doc_start plus lit_len is greater than doc_len_limit plus 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If doc_start plus lit_len minus 1 is greater than doc_len_limit minus 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let i be 0
    Let ok be 1
    While i is less than lit_len:
        Let docc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, doc_start plus i
        Let docl be proc lc_byte with docc
        Let target be 0
        If i is equal to 0:
            Set target to lit0
        End If
        If i is equal to 1:
            Set target to lit1
        End If
        If i is equal to 2:
            Set target to lit2
        End If
        If i is equal to 3:
            Set target to lit3
        End If
        If i is equal to 4:
            Set target to lit4
        End If
        If i is equal to 5:
            Set target to lit5
        End If
        If i is equal to 6:
            Set target to lit6
        End If
        If i is equal to 7:
            Set target to lit7
        End If
        If docl is equal to target:
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set ok to 0
            Set i to lit_len
        End If
    End While
    Return ok
End Process

Process called "match_literal_ci_long" takes document_text as Integer, doc_start as Integer, doc_len_limit as Integer, literal_ptr as Integer, lit_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Case-insensitively compares document_text from doc_start through doc_start plus
    lit_len against literal_ptr from index 0 through lit_len. Both buffers are
    byte-addressable via memory_get_integer. Used for annotation names whose individual
    letters are written into an inline buffer by the caller rather than spelled out as
    parameters.

    Implementation: Bounds-checks against doc_len_limit, then byte-compares with lc_byte
    normalisation.
    :End Note

    If doc_start plus lit_len is greater than doc_len_limit plus 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If doc_start plus lit_len minus 1 is greater than doc_len_limit minus 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let i be 0
    Let ok be 1
    While i is less than lit_len:
        Let docc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with document_text, doc_start plus i
        Let docl be proc lc_byte with docc
        Let litc be proc memory_get_integer from MemoryLayout with literal_ptr, i
        Let litl be proc lc_byte with litc
        If docl is equal to litl:
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set ok to 0
            Set i to lit_len
        End If
    End While
    Return ok
End Process

Process called "is_recognized_annotation_name" takes document_text as Integer, name_start as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Returns 1 if the byte range starting at name_start and running for name_len bytes
    within document_text is one of the canonical Runa annotation names recognized by the
    block-form tokenizer. The recognized set is:
      Reasoning, Implementation, Performance_Hints, Security_Scope, TestCases,
      Verification, Pre_Conditions, Post_Conditions, Invariants, Examples, Notes,
      References.
    Comparison is case-insensitive on the letter bytes. Underscores must match literally.

    Implementation: Dispatches on name_len to a single case-insensitive literal compare
    via match_literal_ci_letters for short names or match_literal_ci_long for longer
    names. For longer names the literal letters are packed into an inline byte buffer
    first. The recognized-name set is fixed and small, so a small decision tree by
    length is faster than a generic table walk.

    Length buckets, with lowercased target letters:
      5  letters: notes
      8  letters: examples
      9  letters: reasoning or testcases
      10 letters: references or invariants
      12 letters: verification
      14 letters: implementation or pre_conditions or security_scope
      15 letters: post_conditions
      17 letters: performance_hints
    :End Note

    If name_len is equal to 5:
        Note: "notes" = n(110) o(111) t(116) e(101) s(115)
        Let m1 be proc match_literal_ci_letters with document_text, name_start, name_start plus name_len, 110, 111, 116, 101, 115, 0, 0, 0, 5
        If m1 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If name_len is equal to 8:
        Note: "examples" = e(101) x(120) a(97) m(109) p(112) l(108) e(101) s(115)
